This paper belongs to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). The paper discusses a novel problem of extracting cardinalities from text, which is a sub-task of information extraction (IE) in NLP. The proposed method uses conditional random fields, which is a popular machine learning technique in NLP and IR. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also involves some evaluation metrics and experimental results, which suggest that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
